.TH "srpt_build_cmd_rsp" 9 "srpt_build_cmd_rsp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
srpt_build_cmd_rsp \- build a SRP_RSP response
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" srpt_build_cmd_rsp
.BI "(struct srpt_rdma_ch *ch "  ","
.BI "struct srpt_send_ioctx *ioctx "  ","
.BI "u64 tag "  ","
.BI "int status "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ch" 12
RDMA channel through which the request has been received.
.IP "ioctx" 12
I/O context associated with the SRP_CMD request. The response will
be built in the buffer ioctx->buf points at and hence this function will
overwrite the request data.
.IP "tag" 12
tag of the request for which this response is being generated.
.IP "status" 12
value for the STATUS field of the SRP_RSP information unit.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the size in bytes of the SRP_RSP response.

An SRP_RSP response contains a SCSI status or service response. See also
section 6.9 in the SRP r16a document for the format of an SRP_RSP
response. See also SPC-2 for more information about sense data.
